{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Pass 1 (INTENT TAG): module-handoff. Pass 2 (LABEL MAP): module-handoff->Integration. The failure boundary is aggregation/handoff across source clients and summary-input builder, not one pure function. REAL-INFRA: no real OS/network is required; source adapters can be in-process fakes. LLM-DEP: this behavior checks input payload completeness, not model judgment. Rejection gate: rejected System because behavior text focuses on \"content passed to the summary-generation step\" (internal handoff), not real endpoint behavior.","test_description":"Wire real collector/orchestrator modules with three fake source adapters returning distinct markers; assert the exact payload sent to summary generation contains all three sections/values and correct source-to-field mapping.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Pass 1 (INTENT TAG): module-handoff. Pass 2 (LABEL MAP): module-handoff->Integration. This is cross-module error propagation/fallback behavior (source client -> report assembler). REAL-INFRA: unavailability can be reproduced by adapter exceptions/timeouts in-process. LLM-DEP: correctness is fallback-note insertion and continuation, not model quality. Rejection gate: rejected System because behavior does not require proving real network failure semantics; it requires graceful degradation contract.","test_description":"Run the reporting pipeline with two normal fake sources and one fake source that raises unavailable; assert report generation completes, includes a `data unavailable` section for only the failed source, and still includes other sections.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Pass 1 (INTENT TAG): model-output. Pass 2 (LABEL MAP): model-output->Agentic. The failure depends on whether the real summary model preserves/reflects key values; deterministic stubs hide hallucination/omission errors (LLM-DEP yes). MULTI-STEP: only one model decision is required, so not Workflow. Rejection gate: rejected Workflow because behavior text is singular (\"The narrative summary\") and does not require multiple agentic stages.","test_description":"Use real summary-generation model calls on representative fixtures; score whether generated narrative includes/aligns with required key metrics/issues/deploy facts (with tolerance rubric), and fail on omissions or incorrect values across repeated runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.78,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Pass 1 (INTENT TAG): real-infra. Pass 2 (LABEL MAP): real-infra->System. This requires real external boundaries (email transport and inbox receipt) plus full-process wiring. MOCK-HIDE: mocked email/inbox can pass while SMTP/API auth, delivery, formatting, or provider behavior fails. LLM-DEP is not the assertion target here; success criterion is end-to-end delivery/receipt. Rejection gate: rejected Agentic because behavior text asserts \"reaches ... inbox correctly,\" not summary quality.","test_description":"Execute the real scheduled-report command in a test environment using real integrations (or provider sandbox) and verify the message is actually received in the configured inbox with expected subject/body attachments and source-derived sections present.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.79,"Agentic":0.07,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Pass 1 (INTENT TAG): module-handoff. Pass 2 (LABEL MAP): module-handoff->Integration. The core failure is state handoff/persistence across runs (delivery failure -> local save -> retry queue/load). Integration with real local filesystem and two sequential invocations is sufficient. INTEGRATION-BRAKE check: (a) no required real network/OS primitive beyond local file I/O, (b) no AI output dependence, (c) no multi-agentic chain. Rejection gate: rejected System because behavior text requires retry on next run, which can be validated by controlled sequential runs without real cron or real network outage.","test_description":"First invocation: mail sender stub returns unreachable; assert report persisted to fallback file/store. Second invocation: sender succeeds; assert persisted report is retried and sent, then cleared/marked delivered to prevent duplicate retries.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.61,"System":0.24,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
